  "notes": [
    "Removes the Storage section and all related routes, clients and runtime modules.",
    "Replaces storage and memory cards with file-manager-specific workspace information.",
    "Moves Terminal into Administration and restricts it to administrators.",
    "Fixes local API authentication when SQLite is selected.",
    "Removes automatic Linux account provisioning and sudo assignment.",
    "Hardens filesystem writes, uploads and archive extraction against unsafe paths and overwrites.",
    "Adds SQLite login rate limiting and application, database and filesystem health checks.",
    "Adds automated security tests and stronger systemd service protections."
